Key Match Events: Utah Jazz secured a 105-92 road win over the Orlando Magic.
The 92 points for Orlando represented the fewest that Utah has given up this season.
Brice Sensabaugh scored 27 points on 11-of-19 shooting, including 5-of-6 from downtown.
Walker Kessler recorded his 14th double-double of the season with 10 points, 17 rebounds, and two assists.
Post-Match Reflections: Jazz head coach Will Hardy praised the team's effort and maintaining a level head through mistakes.
Brice Sensabaugh credited his teammates and coaches for putting him in the right spots and emphasized playing simple and making the right reads.
Walker Kessler's presence was highlighted by Sensabaugh as a key factor in their defensive success.
Miscellaneous Highlights: Utah Jazz's bench contributed 58 points in the win.
Orlando Magic struggled with shooting, ending the night at 35.7 percent from the field and 29.8 percent from beyond the arc.
